        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 4:47PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 447 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Crosby, or 9 miles northwest of Searcy, moving north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hickory Flat...                   Wilburn...
Crosby...                         Ida...
Dewey...                          Huff...
Sidon...                          Pleasant Plains...
Pickens in White County...        Armstrong Springs...
Steprock...                       Roosevelt...
Dam Site Marina...                Clay...
Rosie...                          Concord...
Pangburn...                       Drasco...
Hutchinson...                     Letona...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
